node.text:
https://smittenkitchen.com/2007/10/butternut-squash-and-caramelized-onion-galette/

Did you miss my IG Live demo of making smittenkitchen.com's butternut squash and caramelized onion galette on Friday, 11/8? Good news! We finally figured out how to share and save it forever on IGTV (thank you to everyone who DMed me with tips). Hope you make it, too! [Butternut Squash and Caramelized Onion Galette on smittenkitchen.com]

node.title: butternut squash and caramelized onion galette

node.text: Steak salads are a weekend favorite of ours because they check so many boxes -- a little luxurious, lots of greens, and a bright vinaigrette makes them anything but sleepy. Add a crusty baguette and some wine and wonder why you don't do this more often. // Skirt Steak Salad with Arugula and Blue Cheese on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: Good morning! Here are some crispy corn tortillas smothered in a tomato-chile sauce, layered with cheese and beans, and topped with perfectly-cooked eggs (I'll tell you my trick) and they bake together into the brunch casserole of my dreams. // Chilaquiles Breakfast Casserole on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: We made it to Friday! Here's what I'm going to do with all of the bananas my kids didn't eat, which, now that I think of it, might have been their goal: A banana bread that's half dark chocolate, half classic and gently spiced, marbled in distinct swirls so you don't have to choose. // Marbled Banana Bread on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: A spectacular tomato sauce that you can make from even grocery store grape tomatoes and if that wasn't enough to sell it, this is a 25-minute dinner and one of the better ones in the category. My Wednesday just got so much easier. // Fusilli with Baked Tomato Sauce on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: Feeling celebratory because I just handed in my manuscript for #smittenkitchenkeepers, a new cookbook for Fall 2022. I can't wait to tell you more about it -- but first, some cake. This eight-layer beauty tastes like caramel graham crackers with a creamy, slightly tangy filling and it's one of the coziest things I've ever made. // Russian Honey Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. node.text: A surprising win in the Dinners For Everyone category, a classic cobb lets everyone at my table assemble their salads exactly the way they want it. node.text: If you can read about something called a magic cobbler that you make more or less entirely in the pan you bake it and not have it in the oven 15 minutes later, you're made of stronger stuff than me. This one celebrates peak late-summer-ness with apples, plums and a cinnamon-sugar lid and it's exquisite served with whatever is left of a scoop of vanilla ice cream after it lands on top of the warm cobbler. // Magic Apple and Plum Cobbler on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. node.text: Wait, come back! I realize that homemade cream cheese may not have been on your agenda, possibly ever, but this is almost criminally easy and fast to make, requiring not a single fancy or random ingredient, and the taste is unparalleled, especially in the flavored cream cheeses. You're going to love it. // Homemade Cream Cheese on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: A thing I've noticed this week is that a lot of people are keenly interested in transitioning to fall foods while I, stubbornly, would like it to be summer for at least the 11 days left in it, and possibly as long as the good tomatoes last. Fortunately, this marriage of American-style tomato soup and French-style onion soup -- that's basically an open-faced grilled cheese sandwich on top -- has something for everyone, no matter what season we're planted in. // Roasted Tomato Soup with Broiled Cheddar on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: What if I don't want to make dinner but I really want to make a chocolate pudding pie instead? Is this an option? Can you tell I'm on deadline? I'm not exactly asking for a friend. The cold, richness of homemade chocolate pudding in a crisp, buttery pie shell with a raft of whipped cream and confetti of chocolate shavings on top beckon, and I think we need to listen. // Chocolate Pudding Pie on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. node.text: Feta, tomatoes, garlic, and chickpeas roast in olive oil until the tomatoes blister and soften, the feta becomes creamy, and the whole mixture is a dream to scoop onto flatbread. It's almost endlessly tweakable and I bet even better now with in-season tomatoes. Dinner should always be this easy. // Baked Feta with Tomatoes and Chickpeas on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile.
